Timmy Time Season 1 ep1-20
Timmy is Shaun's cousin who lives in the farm next door. In this series, Timmy and his friends[2] have to learn to share, make friends and own up to mistakes.[3] They are supervised by the teachers, Harriet the Mother Stork and Osbourne the Father Owl. The show is aimed at pre-school aged children, which the company described as "a natural step for Aardman".[1]

The show is made up of ten minute episodes, which do not feature any dialogue, much like Shaun the Sheep.
